[00:40:57] Participant 6: And yeah, so she's been putting dead animals in the parking lot. Someone else says something else. My neighbour's inconsiderate hussy of a girlfriend who shows up to his house at all hours, to be as disruptive as possible, Carmichael Road. Do we have the letter?
[00:41:24] Participant 5: Yeah.
[00:41:26] Participant 6: Or like, the address, is that…yeah, that's where he lives, the Deputy Sheriff. So, at all hours, to be as disruptive as possible. I swear she knocked over every single thing in his backyard, letting herself into the house. Then, she turned on all the lights, which shine right into my bedroom window. I don't know what possessed her to start playing music so late, but I assume it was intended to annoy me personally. Thankfully, it stopped after a couple of hours, but not before I was robbed of my beauty rest…oh, Nancy, I get you. This isn't the first time they have been inappropriately loud; you'd think they'd have the decency to be ashamed of themselves. But now, they are determined to make a mockery of law abiding residents of this peaceful community. 
 So, that was 6.30 a.m., on the 7th. That's what the noise was, around 2.30 last night. Why so judgemental, Nancy, I agree they should be more considerate of their neighbours, but the heart knows what it wants. Besides, for you to cast the first stone, as if you haven't committed a few indiscretions in your life. Okay, so I think it's maybe her showing up at his house, and well maybe she wanted to, like, have an alibi. I mean, so the Deputy Sheriff was busy. The body was discovered at 6.37, possible dead body called in.
[00:43:16] Participant 5: Yeah, it says here, she was staying at the friend's house, the night that Nick died.
[00:43:22] Participant 6: Okay. Well, I guess she was in the house, or maybe she just played music loudly, and disappeared, to kill him.
[00:43:35] Participant 5: Yeah, because she was like, when I brought up the possibility of foul play, she had absolutely refused to consider Nick had been behaving so strangely [inaudible] , I'm sure he didn't even realise what he was doing. She looked like she was about to start crying, so I didn't stay much longer after that.
[00:43:56] Participant 6: Uh-huh.
